sentences: Conrad Johan Bartholdy  (12 March 1853 – 6 December 1904) was a Danish organist, composer, singing teacher, conductor and author of music theory books.
He was honored as a Titular Professor for the year 1900.
Bartholdy was born in Hammel, the son of the local pharmacist and was active as a student in Århus Cathedral from 1872.
